# Intact Car Insurance Testing

This repository contains the test suite for testing the Intact Car Insurance website.

## Prerequisites

- Python 3.x
- pytest
- pytest-bdd
- Selenium WebDriver
- pytest-html
- ChromeDriver (for running tests with Chrome)

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/VINI1520/intact-car-insurance-testing.git

2. Install the required Python packages:

pip install -r requirements.txt


3. Download and install ChromeDriver from the official website:
- ChromeDriver: [https://sites.google.com/chromium.org/driver/](https://sites.google.com/chromium.org/driver/)

4. Update the `config.py` file with the appropriate settings if needed.

## Usage

To run the tests, use the following command:

pytest --html=interact.html

By default, pytest will discover and run all the test scenarios defined in the `intact_car_insurance.feature` file located in the `features` directory.

## File Structure

The file structure of this repository is as follows:

intact-car-insurance-testing/
├── features/
│ └── intact_car_insurance.feature
├── tests/
│ ├── step_definitions/
│ │ └── test_intact_car_insurance_steps.py
│ └── test_intact_car_insurance.py
├── config.py
├── requirements.txt
└── README.md


- The `features/` directory contains the feature file(s) written in the Gherkin syntax. The `intact_car_insurance.feature` file is located in this directory.

- The `tests/` directory is the main directory for your tests.
  - The `step_definitions/` directory is within the `tests/` directory and holds the step definition file(s) for your BDD scenarios. In this case, the `test_intact_car_insurance_steps.py` file is located in this directory.
  - The `test_intact_car_insurance.py` file, which imports and uses the step definitions, is also located in the `tests/` directory.

- The `config.py` file is placed in the main project directory and stores configuration settings for the project.

- The `requirements.txt` file lists the required Python packages and their versions.

Please make sure that your files are organized in the specified directory structure.

